    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zinc titanate, also known as zinc titanium oxide, is an inorganic compound, a white powder insoluble in water, that exists in several major forms. It is used as an antimicrobial stone or metal coating, a regenerable catalyst, a pigment, and a sorbent for high temperature desulfurization.</Note_Text>
